Discovery & connection strategy
BLE (discovery)

Use BLE advertising with a short payload:

node_id (UUID; hashed if too long), capabilities (Wi-Fi Direct available), last_seen_ts.

Scan at adaptive intervals:

Idle low-power: scan every 10s for 2s.

Active (unsent queued messages): scan more aggressively (every 2s for 4s).

Use background advertising & scanning with Android foreground service for reliability
Wi-Fi Direct (link formation)

When payload > small threshold (e.g., >2 KB) or required for reliable transfer, initiate Wi-Fi Direct connection:

Handshake: requester → P2P connect → group formed (one becomes Group Owner) → open TCP socket(s).

Transfer file/payload over TCP with simple ACKs.

Tear down after inactivity timeout (e.g., 30s).

Important: Keep handshakes automatic but with user settings (auto accept within disaster mode); show notifications when connection made
Reliability, ACKs, and retransmission

End-to-end ACK: receiver responds with ACK(msg_id) over the reverse path if possible or broadcasts ACK via neighbors.

If sender doesn't receive ACK within timeout, re-enqueue and retry with exponential backoff.

Hop-by-hop ACK is simpler: each neighbor ACKs after storing & scheduling forward; sender moves status to SENT when next hop ACKs.
Security & privacy

Encryption: Use symmetric encryption for payloads (AES-GCM). Exchange a short ephemeral key during handshake (ECDH over Wi-Fi Direct channel) or pre-share public key fingerprint in BLE advertise to enable encrypted exchange.

Authentication: Optional pre-shared community passphrase or QR code scanning to join a private mesh.

Privacy: Use ephemeral node IDs or let user choose alias; store only hashed identifiers to reduce traceability.

